id: pm-u5le
title: "SDK author-once manifest synthesis: synthesizeExtensionManifest + assertExtensionManifestMatchesBlueprint"
description: "Complete the declarative extension-authoring loop (compose -> derive -> describe/lint -> SYNTHESIZE). Today deriveExtensionCapabilities computes only the capability set; every other manifest field is hand-synced. Add synthesizeExtensionManifest(blueprint, identity) to GENERATE a complete least-privilege ExtensionManifest from a blueprint + author identity, and assertExtensionManifestMatchesBlueprint() as the STRICT CI guard (errors on BOTH undeclared and unused capabilities, unlike the lenient assertExtensionBlueprint) so a hand-maintained manifest.json never drifts. Author once: write the blueprint, generate the manifest, keep it honest."
type: Feature
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[4]: "area:extensions","area:sdk",authoring,dx
created_at: "2026-06-23T12:17:44.212Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-23T12:32:07.017Z"
author: claude-code-agent
parent: pm-ugqx
resolution: "Both child tasks shipped (synthesizeExtensionManifest + assertExtensionManifestMatchesBlueprint). Declarative authoring loop now complete: compose -> derive -> describe/lint -> SYNTHESIZE -> assert. 100% cov, 4911 tests, verified end-to-end via built dist."
