notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-23T12:32:06.592Z",claude-code-agent,"Design: synthesizeExtensionManifest is the GENERATE verb completing compose -> derive -> describe/lint -> synthesize. It pairs with defineExtensionManifest (which only TYPES a hand-written manifest). Capabilities = deriveExtensionCapabilities(blueprint) UNION normalized additionalCapabilities (for imperative-activate escape-hatch surfaces invisible to static derivation). assertExtensionManifestMatchesBlueprint is the STRICT bookend to the lenient assertExtensionBlueprint: fails on BOTH missing (undeclared, would crash activation) AND unused (over-grant, violates least-privilege). Coverage gotcha: pre-guarding manifest.capabilities with Array.isArray makes lint's declared non-null, so result.declared ?? [] is a DEAD branch -> used an erasable cast (result.declared as ExtensionCapability[]) since the repo has zero non-null assertions in src/sdk and a runtime guard would break 100% branch cov. Verified round-trip via built dist: synthesized manifest activates with exactly its capabilities (least-privilege by construction)."
close_reason: "Both child tasks shipped (synthesizeExtensionManifest + assertExtensionManifestMatchesBlueprint). Declarative authoring loop now complete: compose -> derive -> describe/lint -> SYNTHESIZE -> assert. 100% cov, 4911 tests, verified end-to-end via built dist."
